  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nWe currently create our own LRU cache on top of gossipsub's mechanism for checking previously seen messages. Our implementation doesn't account for published messages and gossipsub only checks for the last 256 messages. \r\n\r\nWe should modify gossipsub to make its LRUCache configurable, as well as store message_Id's as bytes to reduce the memory requirements. \r\n\r\nThis well avoid duplicate LRU caches and also add published messages to cache to prevent us registering our own messages as duplicates (if the the current gossipsub limit is reached)",
